JOHANNESBURG - More than 17-million social grants are paid out to over 10-million people in South Africa, every month.That money often supports extended family members and is stretched, to the very last cent.With many recipients unemployed and completely reliant on their grants, the prospect of that money not being paid out on the 1st of April is daunting.* Gogo Mati has seven young children under her roof. See more on her story on the video report attached above.eNCA